Prep the data for plotting¶

In [2]:
%matplotlib inline

# read in the sample data
df = pd.read_csv("/Users/wei/Downloads/city_ops_exercise.csv")
df.date = pd.to_datetime(df.date)

#calculate the ratio between Opendoor listings and MLS listings
df['od2mls_listings'] = df['od_listings']/df['mls_listings']

#calculate the ratio between Opendoor contracts and MLS contracts
df['od2mls_contracts'] = df.od_contracts/df.mls_listings

#calculate the ratio between home visits and listings 
df['od_visits_per_listing'] = df.od_home_visits/df.od_listings

#calculate the ratio between home visits and contracts 
df['od_visits_per_contract'] = df.od_home_visits/df.od_contracts

#calculate the ratio between opendoor listings tocontracts 
df['od_contract_per_listing'] = df.od_contracts/df.od_listings

#calculate the ratio between mls listings tocontracts 
df['mls_contract_per_listing'] = df.mls_contracts/df.mls_listings

Postive signals¶

Our listing market share has increased steadily in 2017 in all four zip codes for homes under $200k.

In [3]:
#Calculate Monthly listings by zip_code, priced at <$200K
df_monthly = df[df.price_band=='<$200K'].groupby(['date', 'zip_code'])['od_listings','mls_listings'].sum()\
.unstack().asfreq('M', 'ffill').stack()
df_monthly['listing_market_share'] = df_monthly.od_listings/df_monthly.mls_listings
df_monthly['listing_market_share'].unstack().plot( title = 'OpenDoor Listing Market Share by Month, \n For Homes Priced <$200K',
                                                 xlim=['2017-01-10','2017-12-30'])
Out[3]:
<matplotlib.axes._subplots.AxesSubplot at 0x1040b7ef0>

Resale strength is strong for homes under $200k in zipcode A. (Measured by OpenDoor’s resale contracts in proportion to MLS resale contracts)

#Calculate Monthly contracts by zip_code, priced at <$200K
df_contract_monthly_200kless = df[df.price_band=='<$200K'].groupby(['date', 'zip_code'])['od_contracts','mls_contracts'].sum()\
.unstack().asfreq('M', 'ffill').stack()

#Opendoor Daily Listings by market
df.pivot_table(index='date', columns = 'zip_code', values='od_listings', aggfunc=sum ).\
resample('7D').mean().plot(title='Opendoor Daily Listing Count by Zipcode\n plotted by week',
                           xlim=['2017-01-10','2017-12-30'])

<matplotlib.axes._subplots.AxesSubplot at 0x10b080cf8>

The gains in listing counts for homes priced under 200K were offset by larger declines in listings for homes priced $200K and more.
